        "description": "With about three years of experience in quality assurance testing within the sports betting industry, I have honed my skills in testing desktop and mobile web pages, applications, and gambling terminals. I have been an integral part of various projects, serving both as a team member and as projects' QA lead. My responsibilities have included performing functional and user interface regression, sanity, smoke and exploratory cross-platform testing, defect investigation, recording, verification and tracking via Jira, and on-site supporting customers in UAT, training and demonstrations periods in North America and Canada. I have also gained hands-on experience in minor automation testing using Selenium IDE and managing API environments and collections in Postman. My deep understanding of company tools has allowed me to train team members and provide continuous support, ensuring the successful execution and delivery of projects. Additionally, I have actively collaborated with different departments, setting up as well as maintaining environments, and created reports and manuals to support the project's progress. My expertise in analyzing Business User Stories (BUSs) to design, maintain, and execute comprehensive tests has contributed significantly to delivering high-quality solutions.",
